abstract: If its after-hours parties are any indication, Wall Street is officially back in business. Thursday night, a few hours after the Dow Jones Industrial Average closed at a two-year high, 350 finance professionals and their guests packed into Simyone Lounge in Manhattan for the annual Young Wall Street charity gala.
